snippet.textDisplay: @tavarish The fuel gauge bouncing up and down randomly is fixed by replacing the fuel pump. The sending unit for the fuel level wears out. The sending unit is ~$90 from the dealer and a new pump is ~$250. You have to drop the tank and pull the pump, so it is worth replacing the whole pump. Also, do not buy after market fuel pumps, I had 2 fail in 2 years on a 96 Dodge Grand Caravan. (Napa fuel pumps).
snippet.textOriginal: @tavarish The fuel gauge bouncing up and down randomly is fixed by replacing the fuel pump. The sending unit for the fuel level wears out. The sending unit is ~$90 from the dealer and a new pump is ~$250. You have to drop the tank and pull the pump, so it is worth replacing the whole pump. Also, do not buy after market fuel pumps, I had 2 fail in 2 years on a 96 Dodge Grand Caravan. (Napa fuel pumps).
